sols_latex:
Notice that we cannot simply plug in $x = 3$ as we will get $B = 0/0$,
an indeterminate form.

To evaluate this limit, factor the numerator and denominator of the
fraction as much as possible:

\begin{align*}
B = \lim_{x \to 3}\frac{x^{2} - 2x - 3}{x^{2} - 3x} = \lim_{x \to 3}\frac{(x - 3)(x + 1)}{(x - 3)x}.
\end{align*}

Notice that there is a term that can be cancelled out from the numerator
and denominator and rewrite the limit:

\begin{align*}
B = \lim_{x \to 3}\frac{x + 1}{x}.
\end{align*} Using the properties of limits,
we can now evaluate this limit by plugging in the value $x = 3$

\begin{align*}
B = \frac{\lim_{x \to 3} x + 1}{\lim_{x \to 3} x} = \frac{4}{3} \quad \rightarrow \quad {\color{blue}B =\frac{4}{3}}.
\end{align*}

